		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31640291">I just found Durarara!! to be a disappointment all around. It had everything it needed to be a favourite of mine: great visuals, a cool and modern soundtrack, larger than life characters who had potential for great development, several intertwining storylines and most importantly the writer for Baccano!, arguably one of the greatest anime in existence.<br />
<br />
Then I watched episode 1... (spoilers ahead)<br />
<div class="spoiler"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.nextSibling.nextSibling.style.display='block';this.style.display='none';" value="Show spoiler"> <span class="spoiler_content" style="display:none"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.parentNode.style.display='none';this.parentNode.parentNode.childNodes[0].style.display='block';" value="Hide spoiler"><br><br />
Okay, episode 1 shouldn't always be the most exciting, but nothing happened. The setting was cool, and the characters were eccentric enough to keep me watching. They alluded to powerful guys that would show up sometime in the future and that was probably the hook.<br />
<br />
Then we finally got to see some of these cool characters. The headless rider, Shizuo who had a huge temper and equally large strength, Izaya who was cold and calculative. So how do we mess up the show from here? Shizuo and Izaya are basically on the back burner for the entirety of the show. The headless rider Celty becomes the most boring character (yet still eccentric) character in the series. I just didn't care for her missing head because her interactions with every character was just so boring and her angst, while justified, just didn't fit with the headless rider persona. Yeah, you've personified an urban myth, but in so doing, you've made her a boring teenager.<br />
<br />
Speaking of boring teenagers, our main 3. There's just nothing interesting about them. They're all your typical teenagers with something special about them. You've got your shy glasses girl, your shy and wimpy main dude and his happy go luck best friend. Yeah they're leaders of 3 warring factions, but it's the factions themselves, their history and the actions they undertake that are interesting and not the leaders. In theory, it's pretty exciting that 3 best friends (stuck in a love triangle even!) don't even know that they're enemies, but when put into full swing in Durarara!!, it just didn't work. It's hard to say why, but I suspect is has something to do with the writer pulling his punches; instead of resolving things the way it was built up to resolve (ie. probably a few deaths and destruction of the city), we get a resolution which I can't even remember because it just wasn't interesting.<br />
<br />
In the end, we're back to where we started. What was the point of everything? The city is back to where it started. The characters are back to where they started bar a bit of development. Celty, the character with the most potential is the most boring character in the show.<br />
<br />
The only reason for my continuation of watching the show was the expectation of something interesting or exciting to happen. It didn't. At least with Baccano!, even when the not so interesting things were happening, the pace was so fast, or the characters were interesting enough that we could get through it no problem. Unfortunately Durarara!! suffers from having no plot to work with so the pace is much too leisurely. It gets boring fast because it decides to focus on the wrong characters.<br />
<br />
That said, it's ridiculousness and sense of style are more than enough reason to keep watching the show. I mightn't have enjoyed it, but I can see why others would. People wouldn't mind the leisurely pace or the boring characters simply because the setting is cool enough to fill that void. It isn't enough for me, but that's just me. Let's hope season 2 will rectify these problems. I'm hopeful it will, we're talking about the guy who wrote the brilliant Baccano! after all.<br />
<!--spoiler--></span></div></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
